# Disable OTP for Agent Login

The goal is to stop the OTP (One-Time Password) requirement for Agent logins, allowing them to log in directly with their credentials.

## Proposed Changes

### [Backend] [auth.py](file:///d:/Hariharan/G-Project/RNT_Tour/backend/app/api/v1/auth.py)

#### [MODIFY] [auth.py](file:///d:/Hariharan/G-Project/RNT_Tour/backend/app/api/v1/auth.py)
- Comment out the block in the `login` function that checks for `UserRole.AGENT` or `UserRole.SUB_USER` to trigger OTP.
- This will allow agents to fall through to the direct login logic that issues a JWT token immediately.
- We will keep the OTP flow for `UserRole.CUSTOMER` as the user specifically requested disabling it for "Agent Login".

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- I will check the code logic to ensure that `UserRole.AGENT` and `UserRole.SUB_USER` now reach the token generation part of the `login` endpoint.

### Manual Verification
- The user can verify by trying to log in as an Agent. They should be logged in immediately without being prompted for an OTP.
